==English==
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# (''[[surfing]]'') [[damage]] on a [[surfboard]], usually in the form of a [[dent]].
#: ''As a kid, I always broke off a chunk of wax and jammed it into a fresh ding in hopes of saving the foam from water invasion, but days later I found myself picking out waxy bits from a brown-stained nightmare.'' &mdash; Jay DiMartino [http://surfing.about.com/cs/surfingfaq/f/050404waxding.htm]
===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|ding||}}
# to [[hit]] or [[strike]]
# (''[[surfing]]'') to damage a [[surfboard]], especially by [[dent]]ing it.
#: ''If you surf regularly, then you're going to ding your board.'' &mdash; BBC surfing Wales [http://www.bbc.co.uk/wales/surfing/sites/features/pages/dings.shtml]
# To mishit a [[golf]] ball

